const confidenceIntervals = "A confidence interval is a range of values that's likely to have the true value of a population parameter based on sample data. Let's say you surveyed a sample of high school teachers and found their average salary was $75,000. Since that's just a sample, you can't say for sure it reflects all teachers, but we can say:\r\n\r\n*\"We're 95% confident that the real average salary for all teachers falls between $72,000 and $78,000.\"*\r\n\r\nThe confidence interval is between $72,000 and $78,000. It gives us a buffer to account for uncertainty in our estimate.\r\n\r\n![Confidence intervals for teachers salaries](https://assets.roadmap.sh/guest/confidence-interval-for-teacher-salaries-mee1i.png)";

