const corsHandling = "**CORS** (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) controls access to resources from a different origin (domain, protocol, or port).\r\n\r\n**Handling CORS**:\r\n\r\n**Backend**: Set headers to allow specific origins.  \r\nExample in Express:  \r\n```javascript\r\nconst cors = require('cors');\r\napp.use(cors({ origin: 'https://example.com' }));\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Frontend**: Proxy API requests to avoid CORS issues during development. ";

