const includeCss = "There are two main ways to include CSS into your HTML, you can either do it “inline” or you can do it with the “style” tag.\r\n\r\n**Inline**: Add `style` directly in an HTML element.\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<p style=\"color: red;\">Hello</p>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Internal**: Use a `<style>` tag in the `<head>`.\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<style>\r\np { color: red; }\r\n</style>\r\n```\r\n\r\n**External**: Link a CSS file using `<link>` in the `<head>`.\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"styles.css\">\r\n```\r\n";

