const nodejsMiddleware = "Middleware in Express is a function that processes requests and responses in the app’s request-response cycle. It can be used to modify request/response objects adding extra information or removing unnecessary data, it can execute code (like logging, parsing JSON, etc) and it can also end the request-response cycle, allowing it to short-circuit the process and return a different response (commonly used to handle invalid or unauthorized requests).\r\n\r\nExample:  \r\n```javascript\r\napp.use((req, res, next) => {\r\n  console.log('Middleware triggered');\r\n  next();\r\n});\r\n```";

