const clearArray = "There are several ways to clear an array in JavaScript. However, I'll focus on the three most common methods.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n// Setting the length of an array property to 0:\r\n\r\nlet num = [20, 30, 40, 50];\r\n\r\nnum.length = 0;\r\n\r\nconsole.log(num); // []\r\n\r\n// Using the splice() method:\r\n\r\nlet num = [20, 30, 40, 50];\r\n\r\nnum.splice(0, num.length);\r\n\r\nconsole.log(num); // []\r\n\r\n// Assigning an empty array:\r\n\r\nlet num = [20, 30, 40, 50]; \r\n\r\nnum = []; \r\n\r\nconsole.log(num); // []\r\n``` ";

