const flushSync = "The `flushSync` function in React is used to flush updates synchronously. It schedules updates to be performed inside a high-priority task, ensuring that the updates are executed immediately and synchronously before returning control to the caller.\r\n\r\n```js\r\nimport { flushSync } from 'react-dom';\r\n\r\nflushSync(callback);\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is useful in situations where you need the DOM to be updated immediately, such as for measurements or to ensure synchronous rendering. However, excessive use of `flushSync` can lead to degraded performance, so it should be used judiciously.\r\n";

